# 🔥 3. Add navigation (like your webview UI)

You control everything via `webContents`:

```js
// Go to URL
view.webContents.loadURL('https://example.com');

// Back / Forward
if (view.webContents.canGoBack()) {
  view.webContents.goBack();
}

if (view.webContents.canGoForward()) {
  view.webContents.goForward();
}

// Reload
view.webContents.reload();
```

---

# 🧩 4. Add a simple toolbar (renderer → main bridge)

## `preload.js`

```js
const { contextBridge, ipcRenderer } = require('electron');

contextBridge.exposeInMainWorld('browserAPI', {
  loadURL: (url) => ipcRenderer.send('load-url', url),
});
```

---

## Update `main.js`

```js
const { ipcMain } = require('electron');

ipcMain.on('load-url', (event, url) => {
  view.webContents.loadURL(url);
});
```

---

## `index.html`

```html
<input id="url" placeholder="Enter URL" />
<button onclick="go()">Go</button>

<script>
  function go() {
    const url = document.getElementById('url').value;
    window.browserAPI.loadURL(url);
  }
</script>
```

---

# 🧠 5. Why this works (and your webview doesn’t)

| Feature        | Webview (VS Code) | BrowserView       |
| -------------- | ----------------- | ----------------- |
| External sites | ❌ blocked         | ✅ full support    |
| CSP bypass     | ❌ no              | ✅ yes             |
| DevTools       | ⚠️ limited        | ✅ full            |
| Process        | sandboxed         | separate Chromium |
| Control        | low               | high              |

